# ==========================================
# C++ AST Visualizer - .gitignore
# ==========================================

# 1. Compiled Executables
ast-viz
ast-viz.exe
*.exe
*.out
*.app

# 2. Temporary Runtime Files
# Catches the GCC stderr dump and the Graphviz intermediate files
errors.txt
*.dot
*.exe

# 3. Generated JSON Data 
# Ignores the JSONs generated when testing the engine so they 
# don't constantly clutter your git commit history.
# frontend/*_code.json
frontend/ast_data.json

# 4. OS & Editor Specific
# Cleans up the background files created by VS Code and Windows/Mac
.vscode/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.log

# ==========================================
# ⚠️ STRATEGIC EXCEPTIONS (WHAT WE KEEP)
# ==========================================
# Note: We deliberately DO NOT ignore *.o files here. 
# Your vendored Tree-sitter files (parser.o, scanner.o, tree-sitter.o) 
# MUST be tracked by Git so recruiters can compile without dependencies.
#
# We also DO NOT ignore *.svg or *.png files because you are 
# hosting the static example graphs for the Web UI and README gallery.